  "notes": [
    "PREPARATION FOR THE MINOR MATH 19A: Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics MATH 19B: Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics Plus one of the following: MATH 23A: Vector Calculus AND MATH 23B: Vector Calculus OR AM 30: Multivariate Calculus for Engineers Plus one of the following sequences: AM 10: Mathematical Methods for Engineers I AND AM 20: Mathematical Methods for Engineers II OR MATH 21: Linear Algebra AND MATH 24: Ordinary Differential Equations Note: Students who complete MATH 21 and MATH 24 are strongly recommended to complete the MATLAB self-paced tutorial .﻿ Please visit the Baskin Engineering Undergraduate Experience website to learn more about this minor.",
    "UC Santa Cruz students may choose to complete one or more minors, provided they can finish all required coursework within their maximum enrollment terms and allowable credits. While a minor will appear on a student's official transcript, it will not be listed on their diploma. Pursuing a minor is a personal decision that should align with a student's educational and career goals. Students do not apply for minors when submitting their application to UC Santa Cruz. After enrolling, transfer students interested in pursuing a minor should contact the department offering the minor for guidance."
